Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @gochujang paste{50%g} to the pan.

Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the black beans, @honey{15%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} into
the frying pan. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season
with @salt{} and @#ground black pepper{} if needed.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{90%g}.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a lightly oiled large #baking tray{} and spoon
the gochujang beans onto one half of each one. Top with the grated cheese.

Fold the other side of the tortilla over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep
together.

Rub a little @oil{} over the top of each quesadilla, then bake on the top shelf of
your oven until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

While the quesadillas bake, cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Add the tomatoes to a #medium bowl{} with the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}
and @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then set aside to macerate.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} in the dressing.

Transfer your quesadillas to your plates and serve the salad alongside.

Add a dollop of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the side for dipping. Enjoy!